1.text: Crease a piece of letter-sized paper in half lengthwise.

2.text: Bring the top corners toward the center crease.

3.text: Fold the angled top edges toward the crease again.

4.text: Fold the paper along the centerline.

5.text: Crease the angled side toward the center fold to create the wings.

6.text: Crease an 8 1⁄2 in × 11 in (22 cm × 28 cm) piece of paper in half lengthwise.

7.text: Bring the top corners toward the crease in the middle.

8.text: Fold the top point down so there’s 1⁄2 in (1.3 cm) left on the bottom.

9.text: Bring the top corners toward the center.

10.text: Hold your folds in place by folding the bottom point over them.

11.text: Fold the paper in half along the center crease.

12.text: Crease the wings down so they line up on the bottom edge.
